</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,294,571]" pageId="8" pageNumber="229">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,583,294,319]" pageId="8" pageNumber="229">Records associated with mangroves:</emphasis>
Pinnacle Rock, Bartolomé Island, Galápagos, mangrove leaf litter; Divine’s Bay south of Puerto Ayora, Santa Cruz Island, Galápagos, intertidal algae from rocks and mangrove roots; Wreck Bay, San Cristóbal Island, Galápagos, decaying mangrove leaf litter; Darwin Bay, Genovesa Island, Galápagos, moist leaves and soil under 
<taxonomicName box="[462,682,402,427]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhizophoraceae" genus="Rhizophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="229" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mangle">
<emphasis box="[462,682,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="229">Rhizophora mangle</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1817" box="[736,1014,403,427]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nyctaginaceae" genus="Cryptocarpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="8" pageNumber="229" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyriformis">
<emphasis box="[736,1014,403,427]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="229">Cryptocarpus pyriformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mangroves (Pfingstl &amp; Schatz 2017).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,487,438,463]" pageId="8" pageNumber="229" type="distribution">
